{{tt+|lt|mokykla|f}}\n* Middle English: {{t|enm|scole}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt+|nb|skole|m}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|szkoła|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|escola|f}}, {{tt+|pt|doutrina|f}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|școală|f}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|уче́ние|n}}, {{tt+|ru|шко́ла|f}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{tt|gd|sgoil}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt+|sh|шко̑ла|f}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|škȏla|f}}\n* Slovak: {{tt+|sk|škola|f}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|escuela|f}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|shule}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|skola}}, {{tt+|sv|lära}}, {{tt|sv|skolbildning|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|aktitud}}, {{tt+|tl|aral}}, {{tt+|tl|turo}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|ekol}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|шко́ла|f}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|trường phái}} ({{tt+|vi|場}}{{tt+|vi|派}})\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|ysgol|f|id=school}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|an establishment offering specialized instruction (driving etc.)}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|шко́ла|f}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|iskola}}, {{q|in compounds}} {{tt+|hu|képző}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|학원(學院)}}\n* Middle English: {{t|enm|scole}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|szkoła|f}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|шко́ла|f}}\n}}<!-- close {{multitrans}} -->\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[educate]], [[teach]], or [[train]] (often, but not necessarily, in a school).\n#: {{ux|en|Many future prime ministers were '''schooled''' in Eton.}}\n#* {{RQ:Dekker Dreame|page=35|passage=''I tooke delights'' / ''In plucking Apples from'' t’Heſperian Trees, / ''Which'' Eating, ''I grew'' Learn’d: ''adde to'' All theſe / ''My'' Priuate Readings, ''which more'' '''School’d''' ''my'' Soule, / ''Then'' Tutors, ''when they ſternliest did'' Controll / ''With'' Frownes ''or'' Rods'':'' {{...}}}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[defeat]] [[emphatically]], to teach an [[opponent]] a [[harsh]] [[lesson]].\n#* {{quote-journal |en |date=April 13, 1998 |author=Leigh Jones |title=National Bar Exam Methods Win in ADA Regulation Test |journal=w:The Journal Record |passage=A blind law graduate who put the National Conference of Bar Examiners to the test got '''schooled''' in federal court.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2006|author=Steve Smith|title=Forever Red: Confessions of a Cornhusker Football Fan|page=67\n|passage=Two weeks later, the Cornhuskers put on their road whites again and promptly got '''schooled''' by miserable Iowa State in Ames. After the shocking loss {{...}}}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2007|author=Peter David; Alvin Sargent|title=Spider-Man 3|pageurl=http://books.google.com/books?id=lQi3QO6h9UoC&pg=PA216&dq=%22gonna+school+you%22&lr=&sig=dpEAXzEMHzrxZQAgCEA0GaPEQDY|page=216|publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn=1416527214\n|passage=\"You again?\" Sandman demanded. \"I guess you didn't learn your lesson.\"<br>\"This time I'm gonna '''school''' you.\"}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=David Yaffe-Bellany|title=Ben McKenzie Would Like a Word With the Crypto Bros|work=The New York Times|date=2022-03-31|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/31/style/ben-mckenzie-crypto.html|issn=0362-4331|passage=Mr. Harris said he was confident he could go toe to toe with any skeptic; he bragged that he’d recently '''schooled''' some crypto haters from Vice News.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en-GB|author=Julian Borger|title=Trump’s rambling Davos speech rehashes warped ideas of US supremacy|work=The Guardian|date=2026-01-21|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2026/jan/21/trumps-rambling-davos-speech-rehashes-warped-ideas-of-us-supremacy|issn=0261-3077|passage=The speech dwindled to a halt and there was a smattering of applause from a gathering that was glad just to have been '''schooled''' for admitting migrants into their country and backing renewable energy, rather than witnessing a full-on declaration of war on the stage in front of them.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To control, or compose, one’s expression.\n#: {{ux|en|She took care to '''school''' her expression, not giving away any of her feelings.}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* [[schooling]]\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|to educate, teach, or train}}\n{{multitrans|data=\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|skool}}\n* Breton: {{tt+|br|skoliata}}, {{tt+|br|kelenn}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|обучавам}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|教育|tr=jiàoyù}}, {{tt+|cmn|訓練|tr=xùnliàn}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|scholen}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|kouluttaa}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|unterrichten}}, {{tt+|de|schulen}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|εκπαιδεύω}}, {{tt+|el|διαπαιδαγωγώ}}, {{tt+|el|διδάσκω}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt|he|לימד|tr=liméd}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|शिक्षण|m}}\n* Interlingua: {{tt|ia|educar}}, {{tt|ia|instruer}}, {{tt|ia|inseniar}}\n* Malay: {{tt|ms|mendidik}}\n* Norwegian: {{tt+|no|skole}}, {{tt|no|skolere}}, {{tt|no|lære opp}}, {{tt+|no|utdanne}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|educar}}, {{tt+|pt|instruir}}, {{tt+|pt|ensinar}}, {{tt|pt|escolarizar}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|învăța}}, {{tt+|ro|educa}}, {{tt+|ro|instrui}}, {{tt+|ro|școlariza}}, {{tt+|ro|antrena}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|учи́ть}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|шко̏ловати}}, {{tt|sh|шко̑лати}}, {{tt|sh|обуча́вати}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|škȍlovati}}, {{tt+|sh|škȏlati}}, {{tt+|sh|obučávati}}\n* Slovene: {{tt+|sl|učiti}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|educar}}, {{tt+|es|escolarizar}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|shule}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|skola}}, {{tt+|sv|lära}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|magturo}}, {{tt|tl|turuan}}, {{tt|tl|sanayin}}\n* Turkish: {{t|tr|eğitim vermek}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt|uk|навча́ти}}\n}}<!-- close {{multitrans}} -->\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-see|to defeat emphatically, to teach an opponent a harsh lesson|humiliate}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{etymid|en|group}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|scole}}, {{m|enm|schole||group of persons, multitude, host, school of fish}}, from {{der|en|dum|scole||multitude, troop of people, swarm of animals}}, from {{der|en|odt|*scola}}, {{m|odt|*skola||troop, multitude}}, from {{der|en|gmw-pro|*skulu|t=troop, group}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*(s)kʷel-||crowd, people}}.\n\nCognate with {{cog|gml|schōle||multitude, troop}}, {{cog|ang|scolu||troop or band of people, host, multitude, school of fish}}. {{doublet|en|shoal|id1=fish}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alt|en|skull||obsolete}}\n\n====Noun====\n[[File:Sixfinger threadfin school.jpg|thumb|A school ({{senseno|en|group-of-fish}}) of [[fish]]]]\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|group-of-fish}} {{cln|en|collective nouns}} {{lb|en|collective}} A group of [[fish]] or a group of [[marine]] [[mammals]] such as [[porpoise]]s, [[dolphin]]s, or [[whale]]s.\n#: {{syn|en|shoal}}\n#: {{ux|en|The divers encountered a huge '''school''' of mackerel.}}\n# A [[multitude]].\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|a group of fish}}\n{{multitrans|data=\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|վտառ}}\n* Asturian: {{tt|ast|cardume|m}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|кася́к|m}}, {{tt|be|згра́я|f}}\n* Breton: {{tt+|br|moudenn|f}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|паса́ж|m}}, {{t+|bg|я́то|n}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|banc|m}}, {{tt|ca|mola de peix|f}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{tt|cmn|[[一群]][[魚]]|tr=yīqún yú}}, {{tt+|cmn|魚群|tr=yúqún}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|hejno|n}}\n* Danish: {{tt|da|stime|c}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|school|f}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|fiŝaro}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|kalaparv}}\n* Faroese: {{tt|fo|torva|f}}, {{tt|fo|vað|n}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|parvi}}, {{tt+|fi|kalaparvi}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|banc|m}}\n* Galician: {{tt+|gl|banco|m}}, {{tt+|gl|manda|f}}, {{tt+|gl|cardume|f}}, {{tt|gl|fieiro|m}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Schwarm|m}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|κοπάδι|n}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt|he|לַהֲקַת דָּגִים|f|tr=lahakat dagim}}, {{tt|he|עֲדַת דַּגִים|f|tr='adat dagim}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|raj}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt+|is|vaða|f}}, {{tt|is|torfa|f}}\n* Indonesian: {{tt+|id|kawanan}}\n* Interlingua: {{tt+|ia|banco}}\n* Irish: {{tt+|ga|scoil|f}}, {{tt|ga|báire|m}}, {{tt|ga|ráth|f}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|banco|m}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|群れ|tr=むれ, mure}}, {{tt+|ja|魚群|tr=ぎょぐん, gyogun}}\n* Khmer: {{tt+|km|ហ្វូង}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|grex|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|јато|n}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|kawanan}}\n* Māori: {{tt|mi|matatuhi}}, {{t|mi|rāngai}}, {{t|mi|ranga}}\n* Maranao: {{tt|mrw|boreng}}, {{tt|mrw|gasang}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt+|nb|stim|m}}, {{tt+|nb|flokk|m}} {{qualifier|e.g. of dolphins}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{tt|nn|stim|m}}, {{tt|nn|flokk|m}} {{qualifier|e.g. of dolphins}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|ławica}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|cardume|m}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|кося́к|m}}, {{tt+|ru|ста́я|f}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{tt|gd|cliath|f}}, {{tt|gd|sgaoth|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|ја̏то|n}}, {{tt|sh|пло́ва|f}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|jȁto}}, {{tt+|sh|plóva|f}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|cardumen|m}}, {{tt+|es|banco|m}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|shule}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|stim|n}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|kulisaw}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|sürü}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|سوری|tr=sürü}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|згра́я|f}}\n}}<!-- close {{multitrans}} -->\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|intransitive|of [[fish]]}} To [[form]] into, or [[travel]] in, a school.\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{pedia}}\n* {{pedia|Shoaling and schooling|school (fish)}}\n* {{pedia|school (disambiguation)}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=chloos|cholos}}\n\n{{C|en|Buildings|Collectives|Organizations|Schools}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/sxoːl/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-school.ogg}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|school}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|oːl|s=1}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|nl|dum|schôle}}, from {{der|nl|la|schola}}, from {{der|nl|grc|σχολή}}. {{doublet|nl|skorro|sjoel}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{nl-noun|f|-en|+}}\n\n# {{senseid|nl|school}} a {{l|en|school}}, educational institution that provides education, whether combined with research or not\n#: {{syn|nl|skorro|q=slang}}\n# a thematic educational institute within a larger one, such as in a university for a single research field\n# any organisation providing instruction\n# a movement or stylistic trend\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|nl\n|avondschool\n|basisschool\n|dansschool\n|hogeschool\n|kleuterschool\n|kweekschool\n|lagere school\n|leerschool\n|middelbare school\n|muziekschool\n|rijschool\n|scholen\n|schoolarts\n|schoolbank\n|schoolboek\n|schoolbord\n|schooldag\n|schoolfeest\n|schoolgemeenschap\n|schoolhuis\n|schoolinspectie\n|schooljaar\n|schooljongen\n|schooljuf\n|schoolkind\n|schoolkrijt\n|schoolleiding\n|schoolmeester\n|schoolmelk\n|school met de Bijbel\n|schoolplein\n|schoolradio\n|schoolschrift\n|schooltas\n|schooltelevisie\n|school-tv\n|schooluniform\n|schoolvakantie\n|schoolvos\n|schoolwerk\n|schoolziek\n|sportschool\n|toneelschool\n}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|af|skool}} {{see desc}}\n* {{desc|brc|skul|sulu}}\n* {{desc|dcr|skoel|skool}}\n* {{desc|pey|skola|sekola}}\n* {{desc|djk|sikoo|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|hns|skul|bor=1|unc=1}}\n* {{desc|kww|skoro|skoo|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|arw|sulu|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|pap|skol|skool|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|srm|sikoò|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|srn|skoro|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|tri|sikora|bor=1}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{inh|nl|dum|schōle}}, from {{inh|nl|odt|*skola}}, from {{inh|nl|gmw-pro|*skolu}}, from {{inh|nl|gmw-pro|*skulu|t=troop, group}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{nl-noun|f|-en|+}}\n\n# {{senseid|nl|crowd}} a [[crowd]], [[group]]\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|nl|samenscholen}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\n{{nonlemma}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|nl|verb form}}\n\n# {{infl of|nl|schuilen||s|past|ind}}\n# {{infl of|nl|scholen||bare-verb}}\n\n{{C|nl|Buildings|Organizations|Schools}}"}}